snippet.title: A very happy wolf
snippet.description:
See more of the woofers on Instagram! https://www.instagram.com/wolf__guard/
Lakomi is an upper-mid content wolfdog who lives in a sanctuary. She was found surviving in the wild at 8 months old, however it quickly became apparent that she had been bred and partially raised in captivity. At the time of her rescue she was wearing a harness intended for an 8 week old. Her skin had grown over the harness and removing it took hours of surgery and months of medication to fight an infection that nearly took her life. When I first got to the sanctuary I was told that she was crazy and wouldn't ever be socialized. Her enclosure has fences that are 14 feet high because she would routinely jump or climb up 12 foot fencing and hang by her jaw at the top. Since I began working on socialization with her that behavior has stopped. She took about two months of daily exposure before she would allow physical contact, but once that wall came down she quickly became playful, sweet, loving, and my personal favorite animal in our charge. Lakomi is a gorgeous example of the redemptive power of love, and being able to know her is one of the greatest privileges of my life. 
A side note: the fur on her belly is thin because she had been spayed several months prior to this video. She is entirely healthy :)

📜Synopsis
Ichiro "Satwo" Suzuki is a game programmer in the middle of a death march. When he was taking a nap during his shift, he found himself in another world. Out of the corner of his eye, he sees a menu screen reminiscent of the game he was working on before his nap. He starts out as a Level 1 player, but also equipped with Map Reveal and Meteor Shower x3 skills, which were just implemented to help new players. While he is busy grasping the new reality before him, a huge army of lizards marches before him! In order to save his life, Satwo uses the Meteor Shower, which gives him a level boost up to Level 310 and a huge amount of treasure.
Be this a dream or reality, Satwo's journey in the new world begins!

This stunningly ambitious series brings to life the most memorable events in the history of the solar system, by using groundbreaking visual effects to tell the thrilling story of all eight planets. Transporting you to the surface of these dynamic worlds to witness the moments of high drama that shaped each one, The Planets reveals how the latest science allows us to unlock their past lives. It pieces together clues of magnificent lost waterfalls on Mars, the mass planetary migrations as they jostled for position early in their history, and even the distant fate of Saturn as one of its moons awakens to form a beautiful water world.

snippet.title: FIRST DRIVE: Singer Goes Turbo – The Whale Tail Returns!
snippet.description:
This is the turbocharged Porsche 911 Reimagined by Singer, and it’s quite a thing!

As with all Singer’s restoration services for the Porsche 911, the process takes the 964 generation of rear-engined, air-cooled cars as its starting point, but the big news on this one is an evolution of the ‘Mezger’ flat-six, now in 3.8-litre from and featuring twin turbochargers.

Owners can specify 450bhp or 510bhp, paired with a manual six-speed gearbox, and personalise their car’s character towards grand touring or sports driving as they wish. But whatever their preference, the gorgeous, bespoke carbonfibre body remains, as does Singer’s exquisite attention to detail.

It celebrates the iconic Porsche 930 Turbo, which so happens to be one of Tom Ford’s all-time favourites, so we sent Top Gear Magazine’s Associate Editor to test this reimagined version…
